# Code Writing Standards

Source code, comments and commit messages must be **English**. See: [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md),
[`.plan/definition-of-done.md`](../../.plan/definition-of-done.md), [`.plan/tech-stack.md`](../../.plan/tech-stack.md).

## General
- Do not change established technology (chi, modernc.org/sqlite, goose, TanStack Query, Tailwind...). Changes require Tech Lead approval + doc update.
- Respect module boundaries ([`.plan/architecture.md`](../../.plan/architecture.md) §3). Build must remain CGO-free.
- Comments explain only intent/tradeoffs/constraints; do not write comments that describe what the code does.

## Go
- Must pass `gofmt`/`goimports` + `golangci-lint`. Wrap errors with `%w`, pass `context.Context`, avoid global state.

```go
// ❌ BAD
if err != nil { return err }
// ✅ GOOD
if err != nil { return fmt.Errorf("scan library %q: %w", lib.ID, err) }
```

## React / TypeScript
- `strict` mode, typed API layer (generated from OpenAPI), component/hook separation, accessibility. Must pass ESLint + Prettier.

## i18n (mandatory)
- User-facing text is **never** hardcoded; resolve via `domain.context.key`. Every feature ships with `en-US` + `tr-TR`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<button>Save</button>
// ✅ GOOD
<button>{t('common.actions.save')}</button>
```

## Test & coverage
- Unit tests required for business logic. Thresholds: core ≥80%, critical modules ≥90%, frontend components ≥70%, e2e for critical flows. `make lint test i18n-check coverage` must pass green before finishing.
